Citation.sTitle: Measurement of Vapor Pressures and Melting Properties of Five Polybrominated Aromatic Flame Retardants
Citation.sAbstract: While vapor pressure is among the most important properties used in the environmental fate assessment of organic contaminants, measured vapor pressures exist only for a few representatives of the group of novel brominated flame retardants (BFRs). To expand on this limited set of data, the vapor pressures of five BFRs--1,2,4,5,-tetrabromo-dimethylbenzene (TBX), 1,2,3,4,5-pentabromo-6-methyl-benzene (PBT), 1,2,3,4,5-pentabromo-6-ethyl-benzene (PBEB), 2,3,4,5,6-pentabromo-phenol (PBP), and 1,3,5-tribromo-2(2,3-dibromopropoxy)-
